ntainer -->\n\t\t\t\t\t</nav><!-- #access --> \t\t\n\t\t\t\t</header>\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"main\" class=\"container clearfix\">\n\n<div id=\"container\">\n\t\n\n<div id=\"primary\" class=\"no-margin-left\">\n   <div id=\"content\">\t<section id=\"post-739\" class=\"post-739 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-technical-thoughts\">\n\t\t<article>\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<header class=\"entry-header\">\n    \t\t\t<h1 class=\"entry-title\">\n    \t\t\t\tTowards natural interfaces    \t\t\t</h1><!-- .entry-title -->\n  \t\t\t</header>\n\n  \t\t\t\n  \t\t\t\n  \t\t\t<div class=\"entry-content clearfix\">\n    \t\t\t<p>Computing indusrry is definitely due for a new interface technology that will\u00c2\u00a0make use of computers more natural.\u00c2\u00a0 Mouse and Keyboards have been with us for quite some time.\u00c2\u00a0 The attached video (thanks, Arjun Satish for sending me the link) from TED conference does look very promising.\u00c2\u00a0 If you like to see exciting interface technology then see this:</p>\n<p><!--StartFragment -->\u00c2\u00a0<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.ted.com/tedtalks/tedtalksplayer.cfm?key=j_han\">http://www.ted.com/tedtalks/tedtalksplayer.cfm?key=j_han</a></p>\n  \t\t\t</div>\n  \t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta-bar clearfix\">\t        \t\t\t\n    \t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n    \t\t\t\t<span class=\"by-author\">By <a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/author/ramesh/\">Ramesh</a></span> |\n    \t\t\t\t<span class=\"date\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/towards-natural-interfaces/\" title=\"6:28 pm\">March 28, 2007</a></span> |\n    \t\t\t\t             \t\t<span class=\"category\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/category/technical-thoughts/\" rel=\"category tag\">Technical Thoughts</a></span> |\n             \t \n    \t\t\t\t             \t\t<span class=\"comments\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/towards-natural-interfaces/#comments\">4 Comments</a></span> |\n             \t \t\t          \t\t\t\t\n    \t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n    \t\t</div>\n\n  \t\t\t\t\t\t<ul class=\"default-wp-page clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<li class=\"previous\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/long-tail-using-recognition-by-crowds/\" rel=\"prev\"><span class=\"meta-nav\">&larr;</span> Long Tail using Recognition by Crowds</a></li>\n\t\t\t\t<li class=\"next\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/phone-as-modern-swiss-army-knife/\" rel=\"next\">Phone as modern Swiss Army Knife <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;</span></a></li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\n<div id=\"comments\" class=\"comments-area\">\n\n\t\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"comments-title\">\n\t\t\t4 thoughts on &ldquo;<span>Towards natural interfaces</span>&rdquo;\t\t</h3>\n\n\t\t<ol class=\"commentlist\">\n\t\t\t\t<li class=\"comment even thread-even depth-1\" id=\"li-comment-956\">\n\t\t<article id=\"comment-956\" class=\"comment\">\n\t\t\t<header class=\"comment-meta comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1865553df482e4fb0657dc4945e73809?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1865553df482e4fb0657dc4945e73809?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' /><cite class=\"fn\"><a href='http://ame2.asu.edu/students/bageshree' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Bageshree Shevade</a> </cite><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/towards-natural-interfaces/#comment-956\"><time pubdate datetime=\"2007-04-02T10:12:57-07:00\">April 2, 2007 at 10:12 am</time></a>\t\t\t</header><!-- .comment-meta -->\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<section class=\"comment-content comment\">\n\t\t\t\t<p>This is really cool!! :).. I am also impressed by how real-time it is!</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><!-- .comment-content -->\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .reply -->\n\t\t</article><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t<li class=\"comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1\" id=\"li-comment-1209\">\n\t\t<article id=\"comment-1209\" class=\"comment\">\n\t\t\t<header class=\"comment-meta comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fe04def8cba87c1c3f72dc416171118c?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fe04def8cba87c1c3f72dc416171118c?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' /><cite class=\"fn\"><a href='http://www.lr-espana.com/reishi/reishi-plus.htm' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Reishi</a> </cite><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/towards-natural-interfaces/#comment-1209\"><time pubdate datetime=\"2007-09-23T04:21:03-07:00\">September 23, 2007 at 4:21 am</time></a>\t\t\t</header><!-- .comment-meta -->\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<section class=\"comment-content comment\">\n\t\t\t\t<p>That is so cool, I hope a company with an ounce of design takes it on (I don&#8217;t think Microsoft would do it justice)</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><!-- .comment-content -->\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .reply -->\n\t\t</article><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t<li class=\"comment even thread-even depth-1\" id=\"li-comment-1346\">\n\t\t<article id=\"comment-1346\" class=\"comment\">\n\t\t\t<header class=\"comment-meta comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2c76b92d1164f36e4ccfe31e5d0ed515?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2c76b92d1164f36e4ccfe31e5d0ed515?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' /><cite class=\"fn\">Hari Haran </cite><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/towards-natural-interfaces/#comment-1346\"><time pubdate datetime=\"2008-01-14T03:57:06-07:00\">January 14, 2008 at 3:57 am</time></a>\t\t\t</header><!-- .comment-meta -->\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<section class=\"comment-content comment\">\n\t\t\t\t<p>Hi Ramesh,</p>\n<p>I own the domain name <a href=\"http://www.naturalinterfaces.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.naturalinterfaces.com</a>. Is it worth having it ?</p>\n<p>Thanks ,</p>\n<p>Hari</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><!-- .comment-content -->\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .reply -->\n\t\t</article><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t<li class=\"comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1\" id=\"li-comment-2237\">\n\t\t<article id=\"comment-2237\" class=\"comment\">\n\t\t\t<header class=\"comment-meta comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/35ebfeb746676043f1d00becbf6a2537?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/35ebfeb746676043f1d00becbf6a2537?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' /><cite class=\"fn\"><a href='http://www.866mymajor.com/Associates_Degree_Business_Degree_z2_2_26_2_1.html' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Associates - Business</a> </cite><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/towards-natural-interfaces/#comment-2237\"><time pubdate datetime=\"2008-06-03T21:13:52-07:00\">June 3, 2008 at 9:13 pm</time></a>\t\t\t</header><!-- .comment-meta -->\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<section class=\"comment-content comment\">\n\t\t\t\t<p>Quite interesting post..!! Well, the potential for the proposed natural interfaces could be seen in various fields, one such is online learning. Computer technology has provided the opportunity to create tools that enable literacy and learning in ways accessible to every possible user.  However these tools need to support sign language interfaces, i.e., ways of input, recognition, and display of signing gestures etc, in order to be fully effective.</p>\n<p>Continuous research work is going on Sign language input and recognition systems for the pat decade or so. Vision based approaches are also under scanner having advantage of allowing the users to remain unencumbered. Recently, researchers have stepped up the process to develop gesture input systems that combine image and device based techniques in order to gather more information about gestures, and thereby achieving more accurate results.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><!-- .comment-content -->\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .reply -->\n\t\t</article><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t\t</ol><!-- .commentlist -->\n\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\t<div id=\"respond\" class=\"comment-respond\">\n\t\t<h3 id=\"reply-title\" class=\"comment-reply-title\">Leave a Reply <small><a rel=\"nofollow\" id=\"cancel-comment-reply-link\" href=\"/towards-natural-interfaces/#respond\" style=\"display:none;\">Cancel reply</a></small></h3>\t\t\t<form action=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/wp-comments-post.php\" method=\"post\" id=\"commentform\" class=\"comment-form\">\n\t\t\t\t<p class=\"comment-notes\"><span id=\"email-notes\">Your email address will not be published.</span> Required fields are marked <span class=\"required\">*</span></p><p class=\"comment-form-comment\"><label for=\"comment\">Comment</label> <textarea id=\"comment\" name=\"comment\" cols=\"45\" rows=\"8\" maxlength=\"65525\" required=\"required\"></textarea></p><p class=\"comment-form-author\"><label for=\"author\">Name <span class=\"required\">*</span></label> <input id=\"author\" name=\"author\" type=\"text\" value=\"\" size=\"30\" maxlength=\"245\" required='required' /></p>\n<p class=\"comment-form-email\"><label for=\"email\">Email <span class=\"required\">*</span></label> <input id=\"email\" name=\"email\" type=\"text\" value=\"\" size=\"30\" maxlength=\"100\" aria-describedby=\"email-notes\" required='required' /></p>\n<p class=\"comment-form-url\"><label for=\"url\">Website</label> <input id=\"url\" name=\"url\" type=\"text\" value=\"\" size=\"30\" maxlength=\"200\" /></p>\n<p class=\"form-submit\"><input name=\"submit\" type=\"submit\" id=\"submit\" class=\"submit\" value=\"Post Comment\" /> <input type='hidden' name='comment_post_ID' value='739' id='comment_post_ID' />\n<input type='hidden' name='comment_parent' id='comment_parent' value='0' />\n</p>\t\t\t</form>\n\t